After seeing Endgame I saw these posters, and they all made sense after the movie.

“One Last Sacrifice” is pretty self explanitory becuase Tony sacrificed himself, and so is “One Last Smash” because we now have professer hulk who does not smash.

We also have “One Last Mission”, which is because Steve is now old and retired. Natasha’s “One Last Combat” was her final fight. She was raised to fight, and now she’s done.

“One Last Fight” must have been Thor getting out of shape (or going with the Gaurdians), and “One Last Shot” was Clint’s last shot at getting his family back.

I mean I don’t know but will you now excuse me while I cry.

description:
Teen and up.

Steve Rogers/Tony Stark

2350 words

#Clint Barton’s Farmhouse of Love

“Okay, here are the pillows… blankets…” Clint tosses the bed sheets on the couch that has been converted into a bed. “Make yourselves at home.”

“Yourselves?” Tony raises an eyebrow.

Barton scratches his head, looking a bit guilty. “Yeah, you see… We don’t have enough room for so many people. Nat and Banner are going to share the bedroom upstairs, and, ah- so you’re sharing the couch.”
